# Feeder App Backend — MVP Walkthrough

Everything is connected end-to-end. This document explains how each piece works, how to connect your Expo app, and how to troubleshoot common issues.

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── index.ts              ← Entry point: loads .env, starts server on 0.0.0.0
├── app.ts                ← Builds Fastify app: registers plugins, routes, /test endpoint
├── db/
│   └── schema.ts         ← Drizzle schema: users, drivers (AutoRider), rides
├── plugins/
│   ├── drizzle.ts        ← DB connection plugin (MySQL pool via DATABASE_URL)
│   ├── jwt.ts            ← JWT auth plugin + type augmentation
│   └── websocket.ts      ← WebSocket plugin + ConnectionManager (in-memory)
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.routes.ts    ← POST /auth/signup, POST /auth/login
│   ├── ride.routes.ts    ← POST /rides/request, PATCH /rides/:id/accept, etc.
│   ├── location.routes.ts← POST /location/update
│   └── ws.routes.ts      ← WebSocket at /ws
├── controllers/
│   ├── auth.controller.ts
│   ├── ride.controller.ts
│   └── location.controller.ts
└── services/
    ├── auth.service.ts   ← bcrypt hashing, JWT generation, login logic
    ├── ride.service.ts   ← Create ride, accept ride (notifies user via WS), status updates
    └── location.service.ts← Driver location → DB + broadcast to user via WS
```

