### 3. Rides (all require JWT)

#### Request a Ride (User)
```
POST /rides/request
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>
```
```json
{
  "pickupLat": 12.9716,
  "pickupLng": 77.5946,
  "dropLat": 12.2958,
  "dropLng": 76.6394,
  "price": 250,
  "paymentMode": "CASH"
}
```
```json
// Response
{ "message": "Ride requested successfully", "rideId": 1 }
```
> This also **broadcasts** `NEW_RIDE_REQUEST` to all connected drivers via WebSocket.

#### Accept a Ride (Driver)
```
PATCH /rides/:id/accept
Authorization: Bearer <driver_token>
```
```json
// Response
{ "message": "Ride accepted successfully", "otp": 2219 }
```
> This sends `RIDE_ACCEPTED` to the user via WebSocket with driver details + OTP.

#### Update Ride Status
```
PATCH /rides/:id/status
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```
```json
{ "status": "STARTED" }   // or "COMPLETED" or "CANCELLED"
```

#### Get Ride Status
```
GET /rides/:id/status
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

