## WebSocket Integration

### Connect
```
ws://<YOUR_IP>:3000/ws
```

### Message Protocol
All messages are JSON strings. Send/receive via `JSON.stringify()` / `JSON.parse()`.

#### Register (first thing after connecting)
```json
// Send
{ "type": "REGISTER", "id": 1, "role": "user" }
// or
{ "type": "REGISTER", "id": 1, "role": "driver" }

// Receive
{ "type": "REGISTERED", "id": 1, "role": "user" }
```

#### Driver Location Update (via WebSocket)
```json
// Driver sends
{ "type": "LOCATION_UPDATE", "role": "driver", "id": 1, "lat": 12.975, "lng": 77.590 }

// User receives (if they have an active ride with this driver)
{ "event": "DRIVER_LOCATION", "rideId": 1, "driverId": 1, "lat": 12.975, "lng": 77.590 }
```

#### Events the User Receives
| Event | When | Payload |
|-------|------|---------|
| `RIDE_ACCEPTED` | Driver accepts their ride | `rideId, driverId, driverName, driverPhone, vehicleNumber, otp` |
| `DRIVER_LOCATION` | Driver moves during ride | `rideId, driverId, lat, lng` |
| `RIDE_COMPLETED` | Ride finished | `rideId` |
| `RIDE_CANCELLED` | Ride cancelled | `rideId` |

#### Events the Driver Receives
| Event | When | Payload |
|-------|------|---------|
| `NEW_RIDE_REQUEST` | User requests a ride | `rideId, pickup {lat, lng}, drop {lat, lng}, price` |

#### Keep-alive
```json
// Send
{ "type": "PING" }
// Receive
{ "type": "PONG" }
```

