## Location Handling Strategy

> [!TIP]
> **User Location** = one-time. Sent when creating a ride request (`pickupLat/pickupLng`).
> **Driver Location** = frequent. Sent every 3-5 seconds via WebSocket `LOCATION_UPDATE` while on a ride.

You have **two options** for driver location updates:

| Method | When to Use |
|--------|-------------|
| **WebSocket** (`LOCATION_UPDATE` message) | Preferred — real-time, lower overhead for frequent updates |
| **REST** (`POST /location/update`) | Fallback — simpler to implement first, works if WebSocket disconnects |

Both methods do the same thing: save to DB + broadcast to the ride's user.

